es of the flatbreads are golden and crispy. Serve with lemon wedges (see Tips)."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Flatbread","content":["20 g olive oil","150 g water","1 tsp white sugar","2 tsp dried instant yeast","300 g baker's flour","½ tsp salt"]},{"title":"Meat topping","content":["3 garlic cloves","250 g brown onions, cut into quarters (approx. 4)","500 g ripe tomatoes, cut into quarters","1 tsp salt","5 sprigs fresh parsley, leaves only","5 sprigs fresh mint, leaves only","1 tsp ground cumin","½ tsp ground cayenne pepper, to taste","1 tsp ground cinnamon","1 tsp paprika","1 tsp ground allspice","½ tsp dried chilli flakes, to taste","2 tbsp pomegranate molasses","500 g lamb mince","30 g pine nuts"]},{"title":"Assembly and baking","content":["olive oil, for greasing","plain flour, for dusting","salt, for sprinkling","2 lemons, cut into quarters"]}],"id":"r314221","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-uzMks6Igegs\/XZQGdI1VgMI\/AAAAAAAAb-M\/hDNLglXQBXwM_ipyrmV4fnUsQczifJdvQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_PpRVuzPkGZ9m_sGA.png","title":"Spiced lamb flatbread","publishedAt":"2018-08-09T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"25.9 g","fat":"15.5 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"44.7 g","calories":"1840.2 kJ \/ 438.2 kcal"},"usefulItems":"plastic wrap, rolling pin, baking trays (30 x 40 cm), bowl, large bowl, wire rack, kitchen towel, oven","hintsAndTricks":["To achieve a crispy base on the flatbreads, ensure your baking trays are hot and well-greased before placing flatbread onto it to bake. This prevents the breads from sticking. Grease and heat tray in between baking of flatbreads.","Freeze any leftover tomato juice to be added to stews or soups.","We suggest squeezing a little lemon juice over flatbreads just before serving.","Accompany with salad and garnish with chopped mint and parsley, if desired."],"basicInfo":["medium","30m","2h","6 portions"]}